&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health Play Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced, enthusiastic and innovative Health Play Specialists to join our expanding Play Service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are required to hold a recognised Health Play Specialist qualification and are registered with HPSET.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require you to manage your workload effectively and efficiently. Candidates are required to have excellent written and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need the skills to support patients with additional needs or challenging behaviour. An awareness and commitment to equality and diversity, responsibility to the safeguarding of children, young people and vulnerable adults in the course of their duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be required to be confident in providing therapeutic play, preparation, distraction and normalised play and demonstrate the knowledge and ability to implement this to our children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be able to plan, co-ordinate and apply therapeutic interventions for children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have vacancies throughout the Evelina London Children&#39;s Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you believe you have the skills, enthusiasm and creativity to join our friendly team we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSusan PrudenJob titlePlay specialist leadEmail addressSusan.Pruden@gstt.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you wish to arrange an informal visit please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan Pruden (Play specialist manager) Susan.Pruden@gstt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
